The paper discusses a method for neural architecture search using Bayesian optimization, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The focus is on optimizing the architecture of neural networks, which is commonly used in computer vision ("cs.CV") and artificial intelligence ("cs.AI") applications. The paper also mentions the use of Gaussian processes, which are commonly used in neural network optimization and fall under the category of "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the development of a distance metric, which could be of interest to the control systems community ("cs.SY").
